{
  "message": "fuzz(corpus): add hand-crafted seeds for snapshot_deserialize + protocol_recovery_state\n\nTwo curated seed corpora harvested from earlier harness-exploration\nruns today, covering the two crash-detector + structural-aware targets\nthat need representative starting inputs beyond whatever a zero-\ncoverage libfuzzer first pass would find.\n\n## fuzz/corpus/snapshot_deserialize/\n\nSix seeds for the existing `fuzz/fuzz_targets/snapshot_deserialize.rs`\ntarget. Named after the snapshot shape each exercises so a reviewer\ncan tell at a glance what branch the seed covers:\n\n* `empty_snapshot.json` \u2014 schema_version 1 with an empty `windows`\n  array; the zero-state case, verifying the deserializer accepts a\n  valid-but-empty session.\n* `single_leaf_window.json` \u2014 one window, one tab, one leaf pane; the\n  minimum representable topology.\n* `nested_split_topology.json` \u2014 recursive horizontal/vertical splits\n  so the pane_tree walker is exercised on non-trivial depth.\n* `multi_window_multi_tab.json` \u2014 cross-window/tab structure with\n  distinct `active_tab_index` values, so the tab-selection path is\n  covered in addition to the pane tree.\n* `invalid_missing_children.json` \u2014 a `Split` node without the\n  `children` field; must be rejected (`Result::Err`) without panic.\n* `invalid_wrong_children_type.json` \u2014 `children` as a string rather\n  than an array; must be rejected without panic.\n\n## fuzz/corpus/protocol_recovery_state/\n\nFour seeds for the `protocol_recovery_state` target added earlier in\nthis branch (104cf257). The naming matches the three pure-synchronous\nsurfaces driven by the harness:\n\n* `delay_attempts` \u2014 Arbitrary-encoded attempt numbers covering the\n  `RecoveryConfig::delay_for_attempt` path the ft-7axpo jitter fix\n  reshaped (including 0, 1, and high-attempt values).\n* `errors_classify` \u2014 a small selection of error messages\n  (\"codec version mismatch\", \"timed out\") routed through\n  `classify_error_message` so the classifier has non-trivial starting\n  coverage rather than fuzzing from zero-entropy input.\n* `empty` \u2014 zero-byte input; pins the degenerate case.\n* A structured seed exercising the `FrameCorruptionDetector` +\n  `ConnectionHealthTracker` op-sequence state machines.\n\nNo code changes \u2014 only new files under `fuzz/corpus/`.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
